00:14:26,023 --> 00:14:31,023
ちょっとこの配信が終わったらエゴサーチをするなり、いっぱいね、見に行くので
Once this stream ends, I'll do some egosearching and look at them,

187
00:14:31,023 --> 00:14:36,023
感想とか、ここが良かったよ、とか呟いてくれたら、とっても嬉しいです！
so I'd be super happy if you tweeted your thoughts or what parts you liked!

188
00:14:36,023 --> 00:14:39,023
ハッピーバースデーありがとう！
Thank you for the happy birthdays!

189
00:14:39,023 --> 00:14:41,023
ふぅ、ふぅ！
Phew, phew!

190
00:14:41,023 --> 00:14:44,023
えー、こちらの配信ですね、あの、タイトル、ライブのタイトル
Also, the title of this stream, the live title...

191
00:14:44,023 --> 00:14:47,023
「In Progress」というタイトルになっています。
...is "In Progress".

192
00:14:47,023 --> 00:14:49,023
ちょっとね、どういう意味かなーって
I'm sure you were wondering what it means,

193
00:14:49,023 --> 00:14:55,023
お前ら、いっぱい推測してくれたと思うんですが、大体合ってました。すごい！
and you guessed a bunch of things, but you were mostly right. Amazing!

194
00:14:55,023 --> 00:15:00,023
こちらのタイトルですね、こちらの英語には「未完成」という
For this title, in English, it has the meaning of "incomplete" or...

195
00:15:00,071 --> 00:15:02,871
意味が含まれていまして、
...has that meaning included in it.

196
00:15:02,871 --> 00:15:09,571
ま、奏のなんだろうな、今の未完成ながら進むというスタンスをこのライブでお見せできればなと思います。
Well, I hope I can show you Kanade's stance of moving forward despite being incomplete in this live performance.

197
00:15:10,071 --> 00:15:23,871
はい、ちょっとまだ自分にこうなんだろう、完全に満足しきっていないけど、まだまだ止まらず今に安堵せず進んでいくぞっていう、そういう意味を込めての「In Progress」というタイトルにさせていただきました！
Yes, I'm still not completely satisfied with myself, but I chose the title "In Progress" to mean that I will keep moving forward without stopping or resting on my laurels!

198
00:15:24,071 --> 00:15:35,071
はい！ま、ちょっとね、えー、駆け足で、えー、紹介していったということで、奏、ちょっとお水飲んでいきたいんですけど、ダンサーさんたち！
Yes! Well, since I introduced things in a bit of a rush, Kanade wants to go drink some water, but dancers!

199
00:15:35,071 --> 00:15:39,571
場を繋いでもらえたりしますかねー？
Could you keep things going while I'm away?

200
00:15:40,071 --> 00:15:43,071
無理？
No way?!

201
00:15:43,071 --> 00:15:47,071
無理じゃない！やるんだよ！
It's not impossible! You've got to do it!

202
00:15:47,071 --> 00:15:52,571
はい、お願いします。なんか面白い動きとか。いっぱいお願いします！
Yes, please. Like, some funny moves. Lots of them, please!

203
00:16:05,571 --> 00:16:06,571
ないしょ。
It's a secret.

204
00:16:06,571 --> 00:16:08,571
ないしょ！？
Secret?!

205
00:16:09,071 --> 00:16:19,571
え、ちょっと、パワハラ奏みたい感じになりましたがですね、あの普段ね、奏のダンスの指導をしてくださっているとっても優しい先生たちですよ、そうですよね？
Well, that felt a bit like Power Harassment Kanade, but these are actually the very kind teachers who usually instruct Kanade's dancing, right?

206
00:16:19,571 --> 00:16:21,071
はい。
Yes.

207
00:16:21,071 --> 00:16:27,571
言わせたみたいな。ちょっと今日の意気込み、なんか「うおー！」とかで言ってもらえたりしますか？
Like I forced you to say it. Could you give us your enthusiasm for today, like "Wooo!" or something?

208
00:16:27,571 --> 00:16:31,071
頑張ります！
We'll do our best!

209
00:16:31,071 --> 00:16:34,071
イェーイ！ダンサーさんたちもたくさんありがとうございました！
Yay! Thank you so much to the dancers as well!

210
00:16:34,071 --> 00:16:39,071
では、では、では。次はゲストパートになります。
So, so, so. Next up is the guest part.

211
00:16:39,071 --> 00:16:42,571
最初は誰かな？
Who will be the first?

212
00:16:43,071 --> 00:16:47,571
ちょっと楽しみということで、じゃ、早速次の曲いきましょう。
I'm really looking forward to it, so let's get straight into the next song.

213
00:17:00,071 --> 00:17:03,071
Party is over

214
00:17:04,571 --> 00:17:09,571
それでも踊りたかった
Still, I wanted to dance

215
00:17:10,071 --> 00:17:15,071
眠れないくらい
To the point I couldn't sleep

216
00:17:15,071 --> 00:17:22,071
情熱の火はいつしか いつの日にか
Before I knew it, the fire of passion, someday...

217
00:17:22,071 --> 00:17:26,571
はなから気付いている 焔はいつか消える
I've known it from the start, that the flame will someday die out

218
00:17:26,571 --> 00:17:29,871
ねぇ なにも要らないはずだった
Hey, I wasn't supposed to need anything

219
00:17:29,871 --> 00:17:33,271
なのにまだ I'm so serious
And yet, I'm still so serious

220
00:17:33,271 --> 00:17:36,071
ああまだ間に合う
Ah, there's still time

221
00:17:36,071 --> 00:17:39,071
ああただ burn it up
Ah, just burn it up

222
00:17:44,071 --> 00:17:47,071
Baby Sorry darling そんなに甘くないよ Bourgeoisie
Baby, sorry darling, it's not that sweet

223
00:17:47,071 --> 00:17:50,071
でもきっとそんなに悪くないよ
But surely it's not that bad

224
00:17:50,071 --> 00:17:55,071
Give me fire Light it up Baby 燃やしちゃうぜ
Give me fire, light it up baby, I'll burn it all down

225
00:17:55,071 --> 00:17:57,071
yeah

226
00:18:29,071 --> 00:18:31,071
Yeah 千代も八千代 変わりもせずに
Yeah, through a thousand, eight thousand generations, without changing

227
00:18:31,071 --> 00:18:34,071
全部燃やせ八百屋お七
Burn it all down, Yaoya Oshichi

228
00:18:34,071 --> 00:18:37,071
出でよ舞えよ火の粉 焚き付けるのが仕事
Come forth, dance, sparks, fanning the flames is my job

229
00:18:37,071 --> 00:18:40,571
燃えるさまはお見事 火遊びはしない ぬるいまね出来ない
The way it burns is magnificent, no playing with fire, no half-hearted tricks

230
00:18:40,571 --> 00:18:43,571
燃やし尽くすマグマドラマ この飽くなき渇き
A magma drama burning everything down, this insatiable thirst

231
00:18:43,571 --> 00:18:46,571
青い炎みたい 死は過去のひとつ隣
Like a blue flame, death is just next door to the past

232
00:20:06,046 --> 00:20:08,046
Turn it up, turn it up, turn it up!

233
00:20:08,046 --> 00:20:11,546
Sorry darling, hurry up... ああ、まだ間に合う...
Sorry darling, hurry up... Ah, we can still make it...

234
00:20:11,546 --> 00:20:14,546
Sorry darling, hurry up... ああ、まだ間に合う...
Sorry darling, hurry up... Ah, we can still make it...

235
00:20:15,046 --> 00:20:18,546
Give me fire, light it up baby, 燃やしちゃうぜ
Give me fire, light it up baby, I'll burn it all up!

236
00:20:21,046 --> 00:20:24,046
Party is over

237
00:20:26,046 --> 00:20:31,046
それでも踊りたかった
But I still wanted to dance...

238
00:20:39,046 --> 00:20:41,546
Wow!

239
00:20:41,546 --> 00:20:44,546
Happy Birthday! / Thank you very much!

240
00:20:44,546 --> 00:20:48,546
Thank you very much! / Birthday girl! / Yeah! Birthday girl!

241
00:20:48,546 --> 00:20:54,046
まず最初のゲストは、Mori Calliope先輩に来ていただきました！
First of all, our first guest is Mori Calliope-senpai!

242
00:20:54,046 --> 00:21:01,046
初めまして！Hi everybody! Yo yo, what's up? It's Mori Calliope here today to celebrate Kanade's special birthday.
Nice to meet you! Hi everybody! Yo yo, what's up? It's Mori Calliope here today to celebrate Kanade's special birthday.

243
00:21:02,046 --> 00:21:06,046
わー！Kanadeの誕生日をお祝いしに来てくれてありがとうございます！
Wow! Thank you so much for coming to celebrate my birthday!

244
00:21:06,046 --> 00:21:09,046
Oh yeah! I was so nervous! / 緊張してた！
Oh yeah! I was so nervous! / I was nervous!

245
00:21:09,046 --> 00:21:13,546
ラップする前、「ヤバい、ヤバい、できない、できない、できない」と思ってた...
Before the rap, I was thinking, "Oh no, oh no, I can't do this, I can't do this..."

246
00:21:13,546 --> 00:21:16,546
いやいやいや、全然感じなかったですよ、そんな！
No, no, no, I didn't feel that at all!

247
00:21:16,546 --> 00:21:19,546
難しい、日本語のラップ...
Japanese rap is so difficult...

248
00:21:19,546 --> 00:21:22,046
めちゃくちゃカッコよかったです！
But you were incredibly cool!

249
00:21:22,046 --> 00:21:25,546
Kanade-chanもカッコよかったよ！
Kanade-chan, you were cool too!

250
00:21:25,546 --> 00:21:28,046
嬉しい！一緒に、いい感じになりました！
I'm so happy! We made a great duo!

251
00:21:28,046 --> 00:21:31,046
一緒に歌いたかったんですよ！
I really wanted to sing together with you!

252
00:21:31,046 --> 00:21:34,046
私も！ / Calliope先輩のラップが大好きで...
Me too! / I love your rap, Calliope-senpai...

253
00:21:34,046 --> 00:21:42,046
あの、「Beyond the Way」でも実は歌わせていただいた、ご一緒させていただいたりしましたから、それ以来じゃないですか？
Actually, we got to sing together in "Beyond the Way", so is this the first time since then?

254
00:21:42,046 --> 00:21:46,546
そうですね。あんまり機会がなくて。でも今回すごかった！
That's right. We didn't have many opportunities. But this time was amazing!

255
00:21:48,546 --> 00:21:51,546
わ、嬉しい！ / ぶちかましました！
Wow, I'm happy! / We crushed it!

256
00:21:51,546 --> 00:21:56,546
ぶちかましました！それ奏もやりたいけど、今スカートだからできないよ。
We crushed it! I want to do that pose too, but I'm wearing a skirt right now so I can't.

257
00:21:56,546 --> 00:22:00,046
スタミナ、スタミナ！ / スタミナ、先輩に分けてもらおう、スタミナ！
Stamina, stamina! / I should ask you to share some of your stamina, senpai!

258
00:22:00,046 --> 00:22:03,546
お水たくさん飲んで！ / はい！ありがとうございます！
Drink lots of water! / Yes! Thank you!

259
00:22:03,546 --> 00:22:06,546
お水飲みにいってこようかな。 / Go, go, yes, yes, yes!
Maybe I'll go get some water. / Go, go, yes, yes, yes!

260
00:22:07,546 --> 00:22:11,546
Hi everybody! Kanade-chan's water time. What's up? I'm Mori Calliope.

261
00:22:11,546 --> 00:22:15,546
Abura... I did it!

262
00:22:15,546 --> 00:22:18,546
Abura!

263
00:22:18,546 --> 00:22:22,046
ちょっと忘れちゃうと思ってたけど、できた！
I thought I'd forget, but I did it!

264
00:22:22,046 --> 00:22:26,546
生歌すごい好きだから、今回誘ってくれてありがとうございます！
I really love live singing, so thank you so much for inviting me!

265
00:22:26,546 --> 00:22:30,546
こちらこそ、ありがとうございます！本当に一緒に歌えてすごく光栄でした！
Thank you so much as well! It was truly an honor to sing with you!

266
00:22:30,546 --> 00:22:32,546
またやろう！
Let's do it again!

267
00:22:32,546 --> 00:22:35,046
またぜひご一緒させてください！
Please let me join you again!

268
00:22:35,046 --> 00:22:38,046
ということで、Calliope先輩ありがとうございました！
So, thank you so much, Calliope-senpai!

269
00:22:38,046 --> 00:22:43,046
ありがとうございました！これからも頑張ってね、good luck! / ありがとうございます！
Thank you very much! Keep doing your best, good luck! / Thank you!

270
00:22:43,046 --> 00:22:45,046
You can do it! Peace! Bye bye! / Thank you very much! Bye bye!

271
00:22:45,046 --> 00:22:48,046
バイバイ！
Bye bye!

272
00:22:49,046 --> 00:22:54,046
ということで、Calliope先輩との『火炎』でした！
So, that was our performance of 'Kaen' with Calliope-senpai!

273
00:22:54,046 --> 00:23:00,046
次の曲行く前にちょっと熱いから、ちょっと着替えてきてもいいですか？
Before going to the next song, it's a bit hot, so can I go change my clothes?

274
00:23:00,046 --> 00:23:02,046
待っててくださいね！
Please wait for me!

275
00:23:08,546 --> 00:23:13,546
ふぅ！ちょっとジャケット脱いできました！ちょっと熱気がすごい！
Phew! I took off my jacket! The heat here is amazing!

276
00:23:13,546 --> 00:23:18,546
お前らもいっぱい、かけ...ありがとう、ありがとうございます！コメント見えてるよ！
Everyone, thank you for all your cheers! I can see your comments!

277
00:23:18,546 --> 00:23:22,546
では、早速次の曲いきましょうかね。
Now, let's head straight to the next song.

278
00:23:22,546 --> 00:23:26,546
ゲストは誰か、楽しみですね。
I wonder who the next guest is. It's exciting!

279
00:23:26,546 --> 00:23:29,046
では、聴いてください。
Now, please listen.

280
00:23:45,046 --> 00:23:49,046
語れない 眠れない トロイメライ
Unspeakable, sleepless, dreams.

281
00:23:49,046 --> 00:23:54,046
あなたの見てる正体
The true identity you see.

282
00:23:54,046 --> 00:23:59,046
誰も読めないカルテ
A medical chart that no one can read.

283
00:23:59,046 --> 00:24:04,546
不可思議 知りたいだけ
Just wanting to know the mystery.

284
00:24:04,546 --> 00:24:08,546
嘘も 現実も
Both lies and reality.

285
00:24:08,546 --> 00:24:13,546
どっちも 真実だったの
They were both the truth.

286
00:25:00,094 --> 00:25:01,394
...カルテ
...chart...

287
00:25:01,394 --> 00:25:05,594
自意識 溢れ出して
...and an overflowing self-consciousness.

288
00:25:17,594 --> 00:25:23,094
鼓動 世界像
Beating, world image...

289
00:25:24,594 --> 00:25:32,094
いつも噛み合わないの
It's always a bit off,

290
00:25:33,094 --> 00:25:37,094
痛くて
it hurts.

291
00:25:37,594 --> 00:25:44,094
毎夜 ねがいごと
Every night I wish,

292
00:25:44,594 --> 00:25:52,094
なんにも疑わないで
I don't want to doubt anything,

293
00:25:52,594 --> 00:25:58,094
混ざり融け合いたい
and I want to melt together.

294
00:25:59,594 --> 00:26:04,594
たわいない 判らない 理由 存在
Silly, I don't know, reasoning, existing...

295
00:26:04,594 --> 00:26:09,094
あなたと残す後悔
Regrets left with you.

296
00:26:09,094 --> 00:26:14,094
誰も読めないカルテ
A chart that no one can read,

297
00:26:14,094 --> 00:26:18,594
不愉快 繰り返して
repeating the unpleasantness.

298
00:26:29,594 --> 00:26:34,594
正しい夢は
Is a correct dream,

299
00:26:35,094 --> 00:26:39,594
かなしい声は
a sad voice,

300
00:26:40,094 --> 00:26:47,094
美しい? 疑わしい? 羨ましい?
beautiful? Doubtful? Enviable?

301
00:26:48,094 --> 00:26:51,594
ねえ、どれ?
Hey, which one?

302
00:26:51,594 --> 00:26:56,594
語れない眠れないトロイメライ
I can't talk, I can't sleep, Traumerei,

303
00:26:56,594 --> 00:27:01,594
あなたの見てる正体
the true identity you are seeing.

304
00:27:01,594 --> 00:27:06,594
誰も読めないカルテ
A chart that no one can read.

305
00:27:06,594 --> 00:27:11,594
不可思議 知りたいだけ
I just want to know the wonder.

306
00:27:11,594 --> 00:27:16,594
終わらないことはない トロイメライ
There is nothing that doesn't end, Traumerei,

307
00:27:16,594 --> 00:27:21,094
あなたと跨ぐ境界
the boundary I cross with you.

308
00:27:21,094 --> 00:27:26,094
誰も読めないカルテ
A chart that no one can read.

309
00:27:26,094 --> 00:27:31,094
思春期 疵口 胸のうち
Adolescence, wounds, inside my chest...

310
00:27:31,094 --> 00:27:36,594
不可思議 知りたいだけ
I just want to know the wonder.

311
00:27:43,594 --> 00:27:46,594
はい！ということで！
Yes! And with that!

312
00:27:46,594 --> 00:27:50,594
にじさんじから町田ちまさんに来ていただきましたー！
From Nijisanji, we have Machita Chima-san here with us!

313
00:27:50,594 --> 00:27:56,594
おまえらの皆さん、こんばんは！上から読んでも下から読んでも町田ちまです！
Good evening to all of Omaera! Whether you read it forward or backward, I'm Machita Chima!

314
00:27:56,594 --> 00:28:00,094
わーい！ちまさんにも「おまえら」が浸透してる！
Yay! "Omaera" has reached Chima-san as well!

315
00:28:00,094 --> 00:28:01,294
もちろん知っています！
Of course I know!

316
00:28:01,294 --> 00:28:02,594
知ってるんですか？
You knew?!

317
00:28:02,594 --> 00:28:04,594
お誕生日おめでとうございます！
Happy birthday!

318
00:28:04,594 --> 00:28:05,594
ありがとうございます！
Thank you so much!

319
00:28:05,594 --> 00:28:07,594
めでたいめでたい
Congratulations, congratulations!

320
00:28:07,594 --> 00:28:08,594
何ですか、その動きは？
What is that movement?

321
00:28:08,594 --> 00:28:10,094
あ、これやっちゃうんです、これ
Ah, I just end up doing this.

322
00:28:10,094 --> 00:28:11,594
あ、やっちゃう...癖なんですか？
Ah, you do... Is it a habit?

323
00:28:11,594 --> 00:28:12,594
癖なんです
It's a habit.

324
00:28:12,594 --> 00:28:14,594
それ、ちょっとリハーサルの時もやってて...
You were doing that during the rehearsal too...

325
00:28:14,594 --> 00:28:16,894
やめて、ばらすのやめてください！
Stop, please don't expose me!

326
00:28:16,894 --> 00:28:19,594
変な動きが出るんですね
So you make weird movements, I see.

327
00:28:19,594 --> 00:28:23,594
うん、でも今日はちょっと大人しくね、お話します
Yeah, but today I'll talk a bit more calmly.

328
00:28:23,594 --> 00:28:27,594
なるほど、ちょっと出てましたけど、全然出してもらっても大丈夫ですからね
I see. It slipped out a bit, but it's totally fine to show it!

329
00:28:27,594 --> 00:28:36,094
あの、そういえば、ちまさんとはですね、先日、一緒に「空想列車」という楽曲の「歌ってみた」をコラボさせていただきまして...
Um, by the way, with Chima-san, we recently collaborated on a cover of the song "Kuusou Ressha"...

330
00:28:36,094 --> 00:28:37,094
せていただきました！
We did!

331
00:28:37,094 --> 00:28:38,294
本当にありがとうございました！
Thank you so much!

332
00:28:38,294 --> 00:28:41,094
こちらこそ、お誘いいただいて本当に嬉しかった！
Likewise, I was so happy you invited me!

333
00:28:41,094 --> 00:28:43,094
そうですか？やったー！
Really? Yay!

334
00:28:43,094 --> 00:28:48,594
もう、ちまさんの透明な歌声に絶対に似合うだろうなと思って...
I thought it would absolutely suit Chima-san's clear singing voice...

335
00:28:48,594 --> 00:28:54,094
「空想列車」もそうだし、今回の「不可思議のカルテ」も絶対に似合うだろうなと思って選曲させていただきました
so I chose both "Kuusou Ressha" and this time's "Fukashigi no Karte."

336
00:28:54,094 --> 00:28:55,594
嬉しい！
I'm so happy!

337
00:28:55,594 --> 00:28:57,894
一緒に歌えてとっても嬉しいです！
I'm so happy we could sing together!

338
00:28:57,894 --> 00:28:59,594
私も幸せです！
I'm happy too!

339
00:28:59,594 --> 00:29:02,594
でも、からで、なんか一個気になってることがあって...
But, there's one thing I've been wondering about...

340
00:29:02,594 --> 00:29:03,294
何でしょう？
What is it?

341
00:29:03,294 --> 00:29:09,594
空想列車のコメント欄に、なんか、「化け物」って書いてあったんですけど、ちまさんのこと。
In the comment section of "Kuusou Ressha," someone wrote "monster" about Chima-san.

342
00:29:09,594 --> 00:29:10,094
うん
Yes.

343
00:29:10,094 --> 00:29:11,294
それは何なんですか？
What's up with that?

344
00:29:11,294 --> 00:29:17,094
多分、別人？あの、違う人のことを言ってるのかなって思うので、忘れてください。
Maybe it's another person? I think they're talking about someone else, so please forget it.

345
00:29:17,094 --> 00:29:21,094
わかりました！そんな、こんな、こんな綺麗な、お姉さん...
Understood! There's no way such a beautiful lady...

346
00:29:21,094 --> 00:29:22,094
そうよ、こんな、もうね...
Right, someone like this...

347
00:29:22,094 --> 00:29:28,094
化け物なわけないですよね、今のコメントでも「化け物」って書いてあったけど、ちょっと見間違えてますよね、これ。
There's no way she's a monster. Though "monster" was written in the comments just now, they must be mistaken.

348
00:29:28,094 --> 00:29:31,094
見間違えたよね、我々二人とも清楚だもんね。
They must have made a mistake. We are both pure and wholesome, after all.

349
00:29:31,094 --> 00:29:34,594
もちろん！からでも清楚ですよ、そりゃあもう！
Of course! Kanade is pure too, absolutely!

350
00:29:34,594 --> 00:29:35,594
はい！
Yes!

351
00:29:35,594 --> 00:29:38,594
ということで、ちまさん、一緒に歌えてとっても嬉しかったかったです！
So, Chima-san, I was so happy to sing with you!

352
00:29:38,594 --> 00:29:40,294
こちらこそ！嬉しかった！
Me too! I was so happy!

353
00:29:40,294 --> 00:29:44,294
嬉しかったです。よかったらまた、機会があったらまた、一緒に歌わせてください！
I was so happy. If you'd like, and if there's another opportunity, please let us sing together again!

354
00:29:44,294 --> 00:29:45,594
いつでも歌いましょう！
Let's sing anytime!

355
00:29:45,594 --> 00:29:48,094
やったー！言質取りました！
Yay! I got you on record!

356
00:29:48,094 --> 00:29:50,094
やったやった！嬉しい。
Yay, yay! I'm happy.

357
00:29:50,094 --> 00:29:52,594
じゃあ、この後も引き続き頑張ってください！
Well then, please keep doing your best for the rest of the show!

358
00:29:52,594 --> 00:29:53,594
ありがとうございます！
Thank you so much!

359
00:29:53,594 --> 00:29:54,594
応援してます！
I'm cheering for you!

360
00:29:54,594 --> 00:29:57,094
ありがとうございます！まったねー！
Thank you! See you later!

361
00:29:57,094 --> 00:29:59,994
またねー！
See you!

362
00:30:01,569 --> 00:30:05,569
ということで、ちょっと奏もお水を飲んできてもいいですか？
So, can Kanade go drink some water too?

363
00:30:05,569 --> 00:30:08,569
ちょっとだけお水飲んできます。
I'll go drink just a little bit of water.

364
00:30:15,569 --> 00:30:19,569
まだまだまだまだ続いていきますよ！
We're still keeping this going!

365
00:30:19,569 --> 00:30:23,569
次は誰かしら？あと二人ですね。
Who's next? There are two people left.

366
00:30:23,569 --> 00:30:27,569
1/2の確率。それでは楽しみにしてください。
A 1 in 2 chance. Well, please look forward to it.

367
00:30:27,569 --> 00:30:30,869
次の曲、行くぞ！
The next song... Here we go!

368
00:30:45,069 --> 00:30:48,069
G4L

369
00:30:51,069 --> 00:30:53,069
あれが正解なんて
Are those the right answers?

370
00:30:53,069 --> 00:30:56,569
誰の成れの果て？（なんだっての悶々々）
Whose end results are those? (What's with this, sigh sigh sigh)

371
00:30:57,069 --> 00:30:58,569
答えも欲しいのも一個てこれだけ
Answers and things I want, one of them, just this much

372
00:30:58,569 --> 00:31:01,069
悩んだってしょうがないじゃんね
It's no use worrying about it, you know

373
00:31:01,069 --> 00:31:05,069
あれは夢だったって思うことにしたって（つら）
Even if I decided to think that was just a dream (pain)

374
00:31:05,069 --> 00:31:08,069
でも全然思えないんだけど
But I can't think that at all

375
00:31:08,069 --> 00:31:12,069
助けてよ　フォロワー！
Help me, follower!

376
00:31:12,069 --> 00:31:13,569
抗うだけ
Just fighting back

377
00:31:13,569 --> 00:31:15,069
若さに負け
Losing to youth

378
00:31:15,069 --> 00:31:16,869
next, next

379
00:31:16,869 --> 00:31:19,069
lucky lucky lucky!

380
00:31:19,069 --> 00:31:21,069
（アーリーオ）
(Early-o)

381
00:31:21,069 --> 00:31:23,069
割り切れたらさ
If I could just accept it

382
00:31:23,069 --> 00:31:25,069
（オーリーオ）
(Oori-o)

383
00:31:25,069 --> 00:31:27,569
楽なのに　とか
It'd be easier, or so...

384
00:31:27,569 --> 00:31:30,569
あぁ…もうヤダ
Ahh... I've had enough

385
00:31:32,069 --> 00:31:34,569
なんという新世界か
What kind of new world is this?

386
00:31:34,569 --> 00:31:36,569
あなた以外は
Other than you

387
00:31:36,569 --> 00:31:40,069
あなた以外はいらない　ない　ない
I don't need anyone else, none, none

388
00:31:40,069 --> 00:31:41,569
はらないでよ　バリア
Don't put up a barrier

389
00:31:41,569 --> 00:31:43,069
あるはずなの何か
There should be something

390
00:31:43,069 --> 00:31:47,569
あったならば　happy! jumpin’ yeah!
If there is, happy! jumpin' yeah!

391
00:31:47,569 --> 00:31:49,069
あなたのその手と
Your hand

392
00:31:49,069 --> 00:31:50,569
あたしのこの手を
and my hand

393
00:31:50,569 --> 00:31:54,069
つないだらもう二度と離さないわ
If we hold them, we'll never let go again

394
00:31:54,069 --> 00:31:55,569
あなたのその手があたしのこの手を
Your hand and my hand

395
00:31:55,569 --> 00:31:58,569
掴んだら
If you grab it

396
00:31:58,569 --> 00:32:02,569
以後お見知りおきを my love♡
Nice to meet you from now on, my love♡

397
00:32:03,069 --> 00:32:05,569
これで終わりなんて
Is this the end?

398
00:32:05,569 --> 00:32:09,069
アガれないままなんて（鳴いちゃってポンポンポン）
Without being able to rise (crying, pon pon pon)

399
00:32:09,069 --> 00:32:11,569
どうにかなっちゃえって願って願ってね
Wishing and wishing that something would happen, right?

400
00:32:14,069 --> 00:32:17,069
朝帰りしたり　しちゃわん？どう？
Hey, maybe we could stay out all night, what do you think?

401
00:32:17,069 --> 00:32:19,069
なあもう我慢できん
Nah, I can't take it anymore

402
00:32:19,069 --> 00:32:20,069
pain, pain

403
00:32:20,069 --> 00:32:21,069
痛いってば everyday
It hurts every day

404
00:32:21,069 --> 00:32:23,569
ま、ゆーていけるけどなブルベ夏なんで関係ないな
Well, I can say that, I'm a cool summer type anyway, it doesn't matter

405
00:32:23,569 --> 00:32:25,069
誰よりもネコ
More catty than anyone else

406
00:32:25,069 --> 00:32:26,569
節操ないも結構
Lack of discipline is also fine

407
00:32:26,569 --> 00:32:30,069
あーしはあーしだ見といてよ ready
I am who I am, just watch me, ready

408
00:32:31,069 --> 00:32:35,069
もう今日で終わらせたいなって
I want to end it today

409
00:32:35,069 --> 00:32:38,569
リスタートできたらって
If I could restart

410
00:32:38,569 --> 00:32:40,569
でも無理よ
But it's impossible

411
00:32:40,569 --> 00:32:42,569
もう…
Already...

412
00:32:42,569 --> 00:32:44,569
what’s on your mind?
what's on your mind?

413
00:32:45,069 --> 00:32:47,069
（アーリーオ）
(Early-o)

414
00:32:47,069 --> 00:32:48,569
割り切れたらさ
If I could accept it

415
00:32:48,569 --> 00:32:50,569
（オーリーオ）
(Oori-o)

416
00:32:50,569 --> 00:32:53,069
楽なのに　とか
It would be easier, or so

417
00:32:53,069 --> 00:32:56,569
あぁ…もうヤダ
Ahh... I've had enough

418
00:32:59,569 --> 00:33:01,569
なんという新世界か
What kind of new world is this?

419
00:33:01,569 --> 00:33:03,569
あなた以外は
Other than you

420
00:33:03,569 --> 00:33:07,569
あなた以外はいらない　ない　ない
I don't need anyone else, none, none

421
00:33:07,569 --> 00:33:09,569
はらないでよ　バリア
Don't put up a barrier

422
00:33:09,569 --> 00:33:11,069
あるはずなの何か
There should be something

423
00:33:11,069 --> 00:33:14,569
あったならば　happy! jumpin’ yeah!
If there is, happy! jumpin' yeah!

424
00:33:14,569 --> 00:33:16,069
あなたのその手と
Your hand

425
00:33:16,069 --> 00:33:17,569
あたしのこの手を
and my hand

426
00:33:17,569 --> 00:33:21,069
つないだらもう二度と離さないわ
If we hold them, we'll never let go again

427
00:33:21,069 --> 00:33:22,569
あなたのその手があたしのこの手を
Your hand and my hand

428
00:33:22,569 --> 00:33:25,069
掴んだら
If you grab it

429
00:33:25,069 --> 00:33:29,069
以後お見知りおきを my love♡
Nice to meet you from now on, my love♡

430
00:33:39,069 --> 00:33:42,569
お見知りおきを my love♡
Nice to meet you from now on, my love♡

431
00:33:49,069 --> 00:33:52,569
はい！なんと3人目のゲストは、
Yes! Unbelievably, our third guest is...

432
00:33:52,569 --> 00:33:55,569
同じく、にじさんじから戌亥とこさんに来ていただきました！
also from Nijisanji, Inui Toko-san! We have her here!

433
00:33:55,569 --> 00:34:00,069
まいど！にじさんじ所属公式つよつよケルベロス、戌亥とこです！
Hello there! I'm Nijisanji's official super strong Cerberus, Inui Toko!

434
00:34:00,069 --> 00:34:01,569
いぬいとこさん！
Inui Toko-san!

435
00:34:01,569 --> 00:34:03,069
違う違う、戌亥とこです。
No, no, it's Inui Toko.

436
00:34:03,069 --> 00:34:04,269
いぬいとこ？
Inui Toko?

437
00:34:04,269 --> 00:34:05,569
戌亥とこ。
Inui Toko.

438
00:34:05,569 --> 00:34:06,569
いぬいとこ？
Inui Toko?

439
00:34:06,569 --> 00:34:07,569
戌亥とこ。
Inui Toko.

440
00:34:07,569 --> 00:34:09,569
い！
I!

441
00:34:09,569 --> 00:34:11,069
え、難しい！
Uh, that's hard!

442
00:34:11,069 --> 00:34:13,069
いいよ、好きに呼んでいいですよ。
It's fine, you can call me whatever you like.

443
00:34:13,069 --> 00:34:14,269
いぬいとこさん！
Inui Toko-san!

444
00:34:14,269 --> 00:34:16,069
お誕生日おめでとうございます！
Happy birthday!

445
00:34:16,069 --> 00:34:17,269
ありがとうございます！
Thank you so much!

446
00:34:17,269 --> 00:34:18,269
Happy Birthday!

447
00:34:18,269 --> 00:34:19,269
イェーイ！
Yay!

448
00:34:19,269 --> 00:34:20,269
Nice to meet you.

449
00:34:20,269 --> 00:34:22,569
Nice to meet you too! はじめまして、はじめましてじゃない…
Nice to meet you too! Nice to meet you... wait, it's not "nice to meet you"...

450
00:34:22,569 --> 00:34:23,569
はじめましてですよ。
It is "nice to meet you"!

451
00:34:23,569 --> 00:34:25,569
今日、初めて会いました。
We met for the first time today.

452
00:34:25,569 --> 00:34:27,569
今日、ガチのはじめまして。
Today is a literal first-time meeting!

453
00:34:27,569 --> 00:34:29,569
いるの？今日ガチのはじめまして。
Are there actually first-time meetings today?

454
00:34:29,569 --> 00:34:31,069
いない、いない、いない。
No, no, no...

455
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:32,569
はじめまして。
Nice to meet you.

456
00:34:32,569 --> 00:34:34,069
はじめまして、ちょっと、
Nice to meet you, well...

457
00:34:34,069 --> 00:34:38,269
ね、ちまさんと、カプセル・リレーションの歌ってみたでご一緒させていただいたんですけど、
Well, we did the "Capsule Relation" cover song together with Chima-san, but...

458
00:34:38,269 --> 00:34:41,069
本当の本当の今日、はじめまして。
but today is the real, real first-time meeting.

459
00:34:41,069 --> 00:34:42,569
本当のはじめまして。
The real first-time meeting.

460
00:34:42,569 --> 00:34:44,069
はい。
Yes.

461
00:34:44,069 --> 00:34:46,069
もう今日、はじめましての時、
And today, when we met for the first time,

462
00:34:46,069 --> 00:34:49,069
あの、とこさんが楽屋に来ていただいて、
um, Toko-san came to the dressing room,

463
00:34:49,069 --> 00:34:52,069
で、挨拶に来ていただいて。ありがとうございます。
and came to greet me. Thank you very much.

464
00:34:52,069 --> 00:34:53,569
いえいえ、こちらこそ。
No, no, thank you.

465
00:34:53,569 --> 00:34:56,069
で、なんかその時にお弁当が奏の部屋にあったから、
And at that time, there was some bento in Kanade's room, so

466
00:34:56,069 --> 00:34:59,069
あ、よかったらお弁当食べますか？って言って、
I said, "Ah, would you like some bento if you want?"

467
00:34:59,069 --> 00:35:00,069
あの、選んでください。カレーだったんですけど、カレーと、なんか付随するものがあるお弁当だったんですけど、
and, "please choose." It was curry, curry and some side dishes in the bento...

468
00:35:00,517 --> 00:35:04,317
なんかトコさんが一言放ったんですよ
But Toko-san uttered a single word...

469
00:35:04,617 --> 00:35:06,417
「芋だ！」って
...'Sweet potatoes!'

470
00:35:06,617 --> 00:35:08,617
お芋が大好きなんです、私
I really love sweet potatoes.

471
00:35:08,717 --> 00:35:09,617
芋？
Sweet potatoes?

472
00:35:09,717 --> 00:35:11,317
そう、お芋めっちゃ好きなんですよ
Yes, I love sweet potatoes so much.

473
00:35:11,417 --> 00:35:13,317
カレーなのに、芋？
Even though it was curry, sweet potatoes?

474
00:35:13,417 --> 00:35:14,717
いや、お芋が好きやから
Well, because I love sweet potatoes.

475
00:35:15,617 --> 00:35:18,517
芋好きなんだって思って、芋があるお弁当だったから
I realized she liked them, and since the bento had them...

476
00:35:18,617 --> 00:35:20,417
「あ、良かった」って思って
...I thought, "Oh, thank goodness!"

477
00:35:20,517 --> 00:35:23,917
じゃあちょっと芋一番大きいの選びますね、って言って
I said, "Then let me choose the biggest one for you."

478
00:35:24,117 --> 00:35:25,717
そう、奏チョイスでね
Right, Kanade's choice.

479
00:35:26,417 --> 00:35:29,917
選んで、別にそれをこう、あげようとしたわけじゃないんですけど
I chose it, not that I was trying to give it to her...

480
00:35:30,017 --> 00:35:32,917
トコさんが、採用してくださって
...but Toko-san accepted my recommendation.

481
00:35:33,117 --> 00:35:34,517
いや、それはするでしょ
Of course I would.

482
00:35:34,617 --> 00:35:38,317
そんな、だってせっかくこれ一番お芋大きいですって選んでくれたら
I mean, since you picked the biggest sweet potato for me...

483
00:35:38,417 --> 00:35:40,117
「あ、じゃあこれで」って
...I'd say, "Ah, then I'll take this one!"

484
00:35:41,117 --> 00:35:42,617
「あ、じゃあこれで」って
"Ah, then I'll take this one!"

485
00:35:42,717 --> 00:35:44,317
「じゃあこれにする」って
"Then I'll go with that one!"

486
00:35:44,417 --> 00:35:46,517
めちゃくちゃ嬉しかったです
I was so incredibly happy.

487
00:35:46,617 --> 00:35:48,917
あの、なんか色んな味あったんですけど
There were actually various flavors,

488
00:35:49,017 --> 00:35:51,317
もう芋の大きさだけで選んでましたよね
but you chose purely based on the size of the potato.

489
00:35:51,417 --> 00:35:52,417
違う、違う！
No, no!

490
00:35:52,517 --> 00:35:54,917
奏が選んでくれたから、持ってったんよ、私は
I took it because Kanade picked it out for me.

491
00:35:55,117 --> 00:35:56,917
感動しました
I was so touched.

492
00:35:58,317 --> 00:35:59,617
えっ、そうなんですか？
Wait, really?

493
00:35:59,717 --> 00:36:00,617
そうよ
Yes.

494
00:36:00,717 --> 00:36:02,117
大好き！
I love you!

495
00:36:03,617 --> 00:36:05,617
よかったら、今後とも何か機会があったら
If you'd like, if there's ever another opportunity...

496
00:36:05,717 --> 00:36:06,717
もちろん
Of course.

497
00:36:06,817 --> 00:36:08,117
なんか一緒にやりましょう
...let's do something together.

498
00:36:08,217 --> 00:36:09,217
いくらでもやろう、一緒に
Let's do it as much as you want.

499
00:36:09,317 --> 00:36:10,517
本当ですか？ユニットも組みますか？
Really? Shall we form a unit too?

500
00:36:10,617 --> 00:36:12,717
もうなんでもやろう、全部やろう。やりたいこと全部やろう
Let's do anything, everything! Let's do whatever we want.

501
00:36:12,817 --> 00:36:14,017
本当ですか？じゃあユニット名...
Really? Then, the unit name...

502
00:36:14,117 --> 00:36:15,917
「カルニス」で
...let's call it "Carnis"!

503
00:36:16,517 --> 00:36:18,317
ちょっとかぶるか
That overlaps a bit, huh?

504
00:36:19,117 --> 00:36:21,317
っていうのは冗談で、なんか
Just kidding, but...

505
00:36:21,417 --> 00:36:23,317
一緒にできたら嬉しいです
...I'd be so happy if we could do something together.

506
00:36:23,417 --> 00:36:25,117
一緒にやりましょう、ぜひ今後とも
Let's definitely work together in the future too.

507
00:36:25,217 --> 00:36:27,617
ありがとうございました、ということでトコさん、ありがとう
Thank you very much. So, Toko-san, thank you...

508
00:36:27,717 --> 00:36:28,917
ございました、この後も楽しみにしています
...very much. I'm looking forward to the rest of the show.

509
00:36:29,017 --> 00:36:31,117
ありがとうございました、一緒に歌えてよかったです
Thank you so much! I'm glad we got to sing together.

510
00:36:31,217 --> 00:36:32,517
バイバイ！
Bye-bye!

511
00:36:35,117 --> 00:36:36,617
ふう
*sighs*

512
00:36:36,717 --> 00:36:39,617
ということでですね、次がゲストは最後になります決まってます
So then, the next guest will be our last.

513
00:36:40,117 --> 00:36:42,117
最後はあの人って
The last guest is that person...

514
00:36:42,217 --> 00:36:44,317
みんな分かるよね？
...so I'm sure you all know who it is, right?

515
00:36:44,417 --> 00:36:46,617
楽しみにしててくださーい
Please look forward to it!

516
00:36:46,717 --> 00:36:48,917
それでは次の曲いきます
Now, let's move on to the next song.

517
00:37:22,117 --> 00:37:28,117
浪漫と算盤
[Song: The sun & moon (Roman to Soroban)]

518
00:37:35,117 --> 00:37:37,917
主義（イズム）持て
Hold onto your principles, hold onto them...

519
00:37:38,117 --> 00:37:44,117
持って利潤をうなしたならば割愛ばい
...if they bring in a profit, let's count it out.

520
00:37:44,917 --> 00:37:46,317
着ない
Never wearing...

521
00:37:46,417 --> 00:37:49,317
学衣ブチ壊し
...cap and gown, instead...

522
00:37:49,417 --> 00:37:53,717
生の真理を宿す
...embedding our lives with truth.

523
00:37:54,117 --> 00:37:56,917
義務解け
Fulfill your duties, fulfill them...

524
00:37:57,117 --> 00:38:03,117
解いて理性を重んじつつも足掻くまで
...while respecting reason, struggle on.

525
00:38:04,117 --> 00:38:05,517
待って
Wait...

526
00:38:05,617 --> 00:38:08,617
漁算割り合えば
...if our calculations agree,

527
00:38:08,717 --> 00:38:12,917
有耶無耶にしていたい
let's keep it ambiguous.

528
00:38:13,117 --> 00:38:14,417
玄人衆
Experts,

529
00:38:14,517 --> 00:38:16,317
素人衆
novices,

530
00:38:16,417 --> 00:38:18,117
玄人衆
experts,

531
00:38:18,217 --> 00:38:20,617
皆々労衆
everyone, the working class.

532
00:38:20,717 --> 00:38:24,717
賛否両論頂戴
Give us both your praise and censure.

533
00:38:25,117 --> 00:38:28,617
お気に召さずとも野暮
Even if you don't like it, it would be unrefined.

534
00:38:31,117 --> 00:38:34,117
新しき技
Always showing off...

535
00:38:34,217 --> 00:38:37,117
毎度繰り出してお相手
...new techniques to our partners.

536
00:38:37,217 --> 00:38:41,317
苦しくとも僕らは解っている
Even if it's painful, we understand.

537
00:38:41,417 --> 00:38:46,117
あなたも同じように
That you, just like us...

538
00:38:46,217 --> 00:38:51,317
独り生きている
...are living all alone.

539
00:38:56,617 --> 00:38:59,317
宇宙を
Showing off...

540
00:38:59,417 --> 00:39:02,117
お見舞いする
...the universe...

541
00:39:02,217 --> 00:39:05,617
向かい合った孤独同士が
...two solitudes facing each other.

542
00:39:05,717 --> 00:39:07,617
自由と
Only freedom...

543
00:39:07,717 --> 00:39:10,317
孤独だけが
...and loneliness...

544
00:39:10,417 --> 00:39:14,317
待っているんでしょう
...are waiting, aren't they?

545
00:39:15,117 --> 00:39:16,517
玄人手
Expert hands,

546
00:39:16,617 --> 00:39:18,117
素人手
novice hands,

547
00:39:18,217 --> 00:39:19,617
玄人手
expert hands,

548
00:39:19,717 --> 00:39:24,617
労働者で生活者の算盤
calculations of the working class, of the living class.

549
00:39:25,117 --> 00:39:30,117
おもしろ可笑しくさせて
Make it funny and amusing.

550
00:39:31,917 --> 00:39:35,117
新しき理
Always painting...

551
00:39:35,217 --> 00:39:40,617
毎度描き出してお相手
...a new truth to our partners.

552
00:39:41,117 --> 00:39:45,117
虚しくともあなたは同じ旅人
Even if it's empty, you are a fellow traveler.

553
00:39:45,217 --> 00:39:52,117
僕は許されていく
I am being forgiven,

554
00:39:52,217 --> 00:39:57,317
夢とうつつを
distorting dream and reality...

555
00:39:57,417 --> 00:40:00,117
歪めて
...to the end.

556
00:40:00,292 --> 00:40:05,192
きっと、そう浪漫抱えたら
Surely, if we embrace romance...

557
00:40:05,192 --> 00:40:09,592
算盤弾いて
and consult the abacus...

558
00:40:10,592 --> 00:40:14,392
両極のど真ん中
aim for the very center of both extremes.

559
00:40:14,392 --> 00:40:17,392
狙い撃て
Shoot to hit.

560
00:40:17,392 --> 00:40:21,092
お願い 勇気をくれ
Please, give me courage...

561
00:40:21,592 --> 00:40:26,592
疑わしい相手なら
Whenever dealing with a questionable partner,

562
00:40:28,092 --> 00:40:31,092
いつだって
at any time,

563
00:40:31,092 --> 00:40:35,892
自分 ずっと進化したいよね
I want to keep evolving myself, right?

564
00:40:36,092 --> 00:40:39,592
答え合わせ
Let's compare our answers.

565
00:40:39,592 --> 00:40:43,592
貴方を知るほど
The more I get to know you,

566
00:40:43,592 --> 00:40:47,592
僕はただされていく
the more I feel corrected.

567
00:40:47,592 --> 00:40:52,592
捨てたものじゃない_
It's not all bad.

568
00:40:52,592 --> 00:40:57,092
ただ 生きようと
Simply striving to live.

569
00:41:47,092 --> 00:41:49,092
うわー！
Whoa!

570
00:41:49,092 --> 00:41:52,092
マイクが遠いぜ。
My mic is too far away.

571
00:41:52,092 --> 00:41:54,092
体震えた！
My body was shaking!

572
00:41:54,092 --> 00:41:56,092
何そのタフな持ち方...
What's with that tough grip...

573
00:41:56,092 --> 00:41:58,592
え、ロッカーでしょ？ / イェーイ！
Eh, you're a rocker, right? / Yeah!

574
00:41:58,592 --> 00:42:00,092
イェーイ！
Yeah!

575
00:42:00,092 --> 00:42:03,092
いや、いいですね。スタンドマイクかっこいいじゃないですか！
Man, this is great. Stand mics look so cool!

576
00:42:03,092 --> 00:42:04,592
かっこいいですよね！
They really are cool!

577
00:42:04,592 --> 00:42:07,092
ね！おめでとうございます、本当に！
Right! Congratulations, seriously!

578
00:42:07,092 --> 00:42:08,592
あ、ありがとうございます！
Ah, thank you so much!

579
00:42:08,592 --> 00:42:11,592
これちょっとウケるんだけど、もう一回いこう。せーの...
This is kind of funny, let's do it again. Ready, set...

580
00:42:11,592 --> 00:42:13,592
ありがとうございました！
Thank you very much!

581
00:42:13,592 --> 00:42:17,092
はい、ということで、最後のゲストはすいちゃん先輩でした！
Yes! So our final guest was Sui-chan senpai!

582
00:42:17,092 --> 00:42:24,092
はい！ありがとうございます、呼んでくださって。
Yes! Thank you so much for having me.

583
00:42:24,092 --> 00:42:28,092
彗星のごとく現れたスターの原石！アイドルVTuberの星街すいせいです！
The star's rough gem that appeared like a comet! Idol VTuber Hoshimachi Suisei!

584
00:42:28,092 --> 00:42:30,092
皆さんこんにちは！ / こんにちは！
Hello, everyone! / Hello!

585
00:42:30,092 --> 00:42:33,092
おとのぜの皆さんなんですよね？
You are all the Otonoze, right?

586
00:42:33,092 --> 00:42:36,592
あ、はい、そうです。正しい正式名称...
Ah, yes, that's right. The correct official name...

587
00:42:36,592 --> 00:42:38,092
素晴らしい！
Wonderful!

588
00:42:38,092 --> 00:42:42,092
ね、おとのぜの皆さんいつもお前らと言われていますけども...
Right, the Otonoze folks are always called "you guys" though...

589
00:42:42,592 --> 00:42:45,592
はい。いや、もう今回の『浪漫と算盤』という楽曲...
Yes. Well, for this song "Roman to Soroban"...

590
00:42:45,592 --> 00:42:51,592
すいちゃん先輩と一緒に歌ったら絶対にカッコいいだろうと思って...
I thought it would be absolutely cool if I sang it with Sui-chan senpai...

591
00:42:51,592 --> 00:42:53,592
まあ、カッコいいけどさ...
Well, it is cool, but...

592
00:42:53,592 --> 00:42:56,592
生でやるもんじゃないよね！
It's not something you should do live, is it!

593
00:42:56,592 --> 00:42:58,592
あははは！
Ahahaha!

594
00:42:58,592 --> 00:43:03,592
もう私本当にさ、昨日とかさ、「歌える？歌える？歌えるかしら？」って、すごく不安だったけど...
Honestly, yesterday I was so anxious like, "Can I sing it? Can I really do it?" but...

595
00:43:03,592 --> 00:43:06,592
今日合わせてみてね、よかったじゃん！
After practicing together today, it turned out great!

596
00:43:06,592 --> 00:43:08,592
よかったです！
I'm so glad!

597
00:43:08,592 --> 00:43:10,092
よかったんじゃない？
Didn't it turn out great?

598
00:43:10,092 --> 00:43:12,592
メチャクチャ美声でしたよ！
Your voice was absolutely beautiful!

599
00:43:12,592 --> 00:43:14,592
メチャクチャ美声でしたよ、お互い！
Both of our voices were absolutely beautiful!

600
00:43:14,592 --> 00:43:17,592
え、ありがとうございます！嬉しい！
Eh, thank you! I'm so happy!

601
00:43:17,592 --> 00:43:19,592
ね、コメント欄もね、うん。
Right, and looking at the comment section too...

602
00:43:19,592 --> 00:43:25,092
「めっちゃよかった」「めっちゃよかった」「相性よかった」ほら、相性よかったって。
"It was so good," "so good," "great chemistry." See, they're saying our chemistry was great.

603
00:43:25,092 --> 00:43:26,592
嬉しい！
I'm so happy!

604
00:43:26,592 --> 00:43:29,592
こうなったらまた歌ってくださいね、一緒に！
Since it went so well, please sing with me again!

605
00:43:29,592 --> 00:43:33,592
え、あ、そうそう、なんか2人だけで歌うのは初めてなんだよね。
Oh, right, this is actually our first time singing as a duo, isn't it?

606
00:43:33,592 --> 00:43:40,092
そうんです。『パンダヒーロー』で4人で一緒に歌うっていうことはあったんですけど、今回2人きりは初めてということで...
That's right. We sang together with four people in "Panda Hero," but this is the first time we're singing just the two of us...

607
00:43:40,092 --> 00:43:45,092
ね、すごい楽しかったですし、またね、呼んでくださいよ、奏ちゃん。奏ちゃんのためならいつでも飛びますよ。
Right, it was really fun. Please invite me again, Kanade-chan. I'll fly over anytime for you, Kanade-chan.

608
00:43:45,092 --> 00:43:46,592
ぜひぜひ！
Please do!

609
00:43:46,592 --> 00:43:52,592
生でハモリという、すごい難しい難題を一緒に飛び越えられて嬉しいです！
I'm so glad we were able to overcome the extremely difficult challenge of doing live harmonies together!

610
00:43:52,592 --> 00:43:53,892
飛び越えたね！
We jumped right over it, didn't we!

611
00:43:53,892 --> 00:43:55,292
嬉しかったですね！
It was wonderful!

612
00:43:55,292 --> 00:44:01,092
頑張りました、私たち！ぜひともね、アーカイブも残るしね、何回も聞き返してほしいですね。
We did our best! The archive will be up, so I hope everyone listens to it over and over again.

613
00:44:01,092 --> 00:44:02,092
はい、ぜひ！
Yes, absolutely!

614
00:44:02,092 --> 00:44:07,592
ということで、奏さん、この後もまだまだ続くと思いますが、頑張ってください！
So, Kanade-san, I know there's still more to come after this, but do your best!

615
00:44:07,592 --> 00:44:10,592
ありがとうございます！本当にありがとうございました！
Thank you! Thank you so much!

616
00:44:10,592 --> 00:44:12,092
ありがとうございました！
Thank you very much!

617
00:44:12,092 --> 00:44:13,592
ありがとうございました！
Thank you very much!

618
00:44:13,592 --> 00:44:15,092
それでは、失礼します！
With that, I'll take my leave!

619
00:44:15,092 --> 00:44:17,592
はい、ありがとうございました！
Yes, thank you so much!

620
00:44:18,092 --> 00:44:22,092
さあ、ゲストの皆さんにね、たくさん盛り上げていただきました
Now, our guests have hyped things up so much,

621
00:44:22,092 --> 00:44:26,592
ということで、ここからはソロでですね、頑張っていきますよ！
so from here on out, I'll be doing my solo performance and giving it my all!

622
00:44:26,592 --> 00:44:29,092
ということで、まだまだ盛り上げていきます！
Let's keep the energy going!

623
00:44:29,092 --> 00:44:34,092
その前にちょっと、準備とお水を飲んでくるので、待っていてください！行ってきます！
Before that, I'll go get ready and drink some water, so please wait a moment! See you soon!

624
00:44:55,292 --> 00:45:00,092
ここからは一気に5曲、いっちゃいます！
From here on, I'm going to perform 5 songs in a row!

625
00:45:00,440 --> 00:45:01,940
最後に...
Lastly...

626
00:45:01,940 --> 00:45:05,240
し、し、し、し、し...
S-S-S-S-S...

627
00:45:05,240 --> 00:45:06,940
シークレットだもん！
It's a secret!

628
00:45:06,940 --> 00:45:09,640
最後のお楽しみにということで。
Please look forward to it at the end.

629
00:45:09,640 --> 00:45:13,340
それでは、次の曲聞いてください。
With that, please listen to the next song.

630
00:45:13,340 --> 00:45:15,640
All Alone With You

631
00:45:28,140 --> 00:45:32,140
All Alone With You / 作詞・作曲：ryo (supercell)
[Song: All Alone With You / Lyrics & Composition: ryo (supercell)]

632
00:45:32,540 --> 00:45:36,340
Yeah...

633
00:45:37,140 --> 00:45:40,640
Ah...

634
00:45:41,340 --> 00:45:47,440
誰かを愛することなんて 出来るわけなくって
There's no way we could ever love someone else,

635
00:45:47,440 --> 00:45:53,140
だけど誰かに愛されたくて
but we want someone to love us.

636
00:45:54,540 --> 00:46:00,740
変わらない昨日がずっと続いたとしても
Even if yesterday went on never changing,

637
00:46:00,740 --> 00:46:04,540
どこにも行けやしないんだ
we can't go anywhere at all.

638
00:46:04,540 --> 00:46:07,640
私とキミ
You and I...

639
00:46:07,940 --> 00:46:16,940
神さま どこへ行ってしまったの ねえ
Lord in heaven, where have you gone? Please...

640
00:46:17,140 --> 00:46:21,140
返事はなくて いつだってそうだよ
...there is no response, it's always like this.

641
00:46:31,340 --> 00:46:33,540
Are you still here?

642
00:46:33,740 --> 00:46:39,940
You'll never walk alone あなたと行く
You'll never walk alone, I'll go with you.

643
00:46:39,940 --> 00:46:44,340
どんな罪も
No matter your sin,

644
00:46:44,340 --> 00:46:47,940
背負ってあげる
I'll shoulder it for you.

645
00:46:47,940 --> 00:46:51,740
道なき道を
I'll walk the unpaved paths...

646
00:46:51,740 --> 00:47:01,540
歩いてくの あなたと二人で
...all alone with you.

647
00:47:14,340 --> 00:47:18,140
こっちにきて 私に触れてキスをして
Come here, touch me, and kiss me.

648
00:47:20,640 --> 00:47:27,140
もっとめちゃくちゃに したっていいんだよ
It's okay for you to mess me up even more, you know?

649
00:47:27,340 --> 00:47:33,940
いつか誰もが死んじゃって 忘れられてくなら
If everyone will die one day and be forgotten,

650
00:47:33,940 --> 00:47:40,940
今確かなものだけを信じるわ
right now, I'll believe only in something concrete.

651
00:47:41,340 --> 00:47:49,140
神さま気取りの人が言うの
Pretentious people who act like gods say...

652
00:47:49,340 --> 00:47:53,540
ねえ 人は強いって
...'Hey, people are strong.'

653
00:47:54,140 --> 00:48:04,740
そんなの嘘だよ
That is a lie.

654
00:48:04,940 --> 00:48:06,940
Do you agree?

655
00:48:06,940 --> 00:48:13,740
I will stay with you あなたの手で
I will stay with you, with your hands...

656
00:48:13,740 --> 00:48:17,540
抱きしめてよ
...embrace me...

657
00:48:17,540 --> 00:48:21,140
思いっきり
...with all your strength.

658
00:48:21,140 --> 00:48:24,540
怖がらなくて
Don't be afraid.

659
00:48:24,540 --> 00:48:28,540
もう大丈夫
You'll be alright.

660
00:48:28,540 --> 00:48:34,340
私なら
I'm here for you.

661
00:48:34,340 --> 00:48:40,340
その手が汚れてしまったとしても
Even if your hands are stained beyond cleansing,

662
00:48:40,340 --> 00:48:45,140
愛してほしい
I want you to love...

663
00:48:45,140 --> 00:48:57,140
私のこと
...me.

664
00:49:27,140 --> 00:49:33,540
You'll never walk alone あなたと行く
You'll never walk alone, I'll go with you.

665
00:49:33,540 --> 00:49:37,540
どんな罪も
No matter your sin,

666
00:49:37,540 --> 00:49:41,340
背負ってあげる
I'll shoulder it for you.

667
00:49:41,340 --> 00:49:44,940
道なき道を
I'll walk the unpaved paths...

668
00:49:44,940 --> 00:49:54,140
歩いてくの あなたと
...with you.

669
00:49:54,140 --> 00:49:59,140
I will stay with you

670
00:50:00,115 --> 00:50:04,615
優しく愛でて
Cherish me gently

671
00:50:04,615 --> 00:50:08,615
思い通り望めない
Since there's nothing but things

672
00:50:08,615 --> 00:50:11,315
ものばかり
that don't go the way I want...

673
00:50:11,315 --> 00:50:14,115
何もないから
...and I have nothing else,

674
00:50:14,115 --> 00:50:19,615
あなたと
I want to be with you,

675
00:50:20,615 --> 00:50:26,615
二人で
just the two of us.

676
00:51:40,115 --> 00:51:44,315
あたたかい涙で
With warm tears

677
00:51:44,315 --> 00:51:48,915
ふいに目覚めた
I suddenly woke up

678
00:51:48,915 --> 00:51:54,615
あぁ 枯れた夢の続きは保存
Ah, where is the continuation of

679
00:51:54,615 --> 00:52:00,315
どこにあるの？保存
the withered dream?

680
00:52:01,115 --> 00:52:04,615
さびしいよ
I'm so lonely

681
00:52:04,615 --> 00:52:07,615
Please give it back

682
00:52:11,615 --> 00:52:16,315
いつかになれば保存
If someday comes,

683
00:52:16,315 --> 00:52:20,615
楽になれる
will I find peace?

684
00:52:20,615 --> 00:52:24,115
寄せては返す
Waves that wash ashore and return...

685
00:52:24,115 --> 00:52:29,615
波に抗って
...I resist them

686
00:52:32,115 --> 00:52:36,115
白い枕に
On the white pillow,

687
00:52:36,115 --> 00:52:41,115
寝ぼけたままの顔
my half-asleep face...

688
00:52:41,115 --> 00:52:44,615
うずめて
...I bury it

689
00:52:44,615 --> 00:52:48,115
同じ夢を
The same dream...

690
00:52:50,615 --> 00:52:54,315
願うほどに保存
...the more I wish for it,

691
00:52:54,315 --> 00:52:59,115
冴えていくよ
...the more awake I become

692
00:52:59,615 --> 00:53:04,615
Please give it back

693
00:53:04,615 --> 00:53:09,615
代わりなんていないよ
There is no replacement for you

694
00:53:09,615 --> 00:53:12,915
あなたの匂い保存
Your scent...

695
00:53:12,915 --> 00:53:15,615
思い出せない
...I can't even remember it

696
00:53:15,615 --> 00:53:21,115
波にさらわれて
Swept away by the waves

697
00:53:30,115 --> 00:53:33,115
夢の続きを保存保存
The continuation of the dream...

698
00:53:33,115 --> 00:53:36,315
捕まえに行くから保存
...I'm going to catch it,

699
00:53:36,315 --> 00:53:38,615
待ってて
so please wait for me

700
00:53:38,615 --> 00:53:40,615
いつの間にか
Before I knew it,

701
00:53:40,615 --> 00:53:42,315
孤独ぶるには
to act all lonely,

702
00:53:42,315 --> 00:53:44,115
優しさに触れすぎた
I've touched too much kindness

703
00:53:44,115 --> 00:53:45,915
沁みていく
It sinks in

704
00:53:45,915 --> 00:53:48,615
顔を上げてみようか保存
Shall I try raising my face?

705
00:53:48,615 --> 00:53:52,115
一人じゃないって
That I'm not alone...

706
00:53:52,115 --> 00:53:55,115
信じてみたい保存
...I want to believe that,

707
00:53:55,115 --> 00:53:58,315
信じてみたいの
I really want to believe it

708
00:53:58,315 --> 00:54:03,315
Please give it back

709
00:54:03,315 --> 00:54:08,315
生まれたばかりの保存
Just newly born...

710
00:54:08,315 --> 00:54:13,115
淡い光に保存
...in that faint light,

711
00:54:13,115 --> 00:54:16,315
希望を見たの
I saw hope

712
00:54:16,315 --> 00:54:18,615
胸が熱いよ
My heart is burning

713
00:54:18,615 --> 00:54:23,615
手を握ってよ
Hold my hand

714
00:54:23,615 --> 00:54:26,615
迷わないよ
I won't get lost

715
00:54:26,615 --> 00:54:28,615
終わり
The end

716
00:54:28,615 --> 00:54:31,615
明日からまた保存
From tomorrow again,

717
00:54:31,615 --> 00:54:34,615
選んだ道を保存
on the path I chose,

718
00:54:34,615 --> 00:54:38,315
進めるように
so I can move forward

719
00:55:31,363 --> 00:55:34,163
おらあ！まだまだ行くぞ！
All right! We're still going!

720
00:55:36,763 --> 00:55:41,363
ぶつかって 逃げ込んで 僕は
Colliding, running away, I...

721
00:55:41,363 --> 00:55:46,663
いつしか ここに立ってた
...before I knew it, was standing here.

722
00:55:46,963 --> 00:55:51,663
誰もが 憧れる ヒーローに
I wanted to become a hero...

723
00:55:51,663 --> 00:55:56,663
なりたくて でもなれなくて
...that everyone admires, but I couldn't.

724
00:55:57,263 --> 00:56:01,163
これくらいじゃ 届かないこと
I knew that like this, I wouldn't reach it,

725
00:56:01,163 --> 00:56:06,163
分かっていたのに
even though I knew that.

726
00:56:07,163 --> 00:56:10,163
敗北の少年 現実を謳え
Defeated boy, sing of reality.

727
00:56:10,163 --> 00:56:15,663
あんな風に 空は飛べやしないんだ
You can't fly in the sky like that.

728
00:56:17,463 --> 00:56:22,163
こんな泥に 意味があるなら
If there's meaning in this mud,

729
00:56:22,163 --> 00:56:26,163
僕らは地を這う
we will crawl on the ground.

730
00:56:36,363 --> 00:56:40,963
耳鳴りか 谺して僕に
Is it a ringing in my ears echoing to me?

731
00:56:40,963 --> 00:56:46,163
奇跡が 問いかけるんだ
Or is a miracle questioning me?

732
00:56:46,663 --> 00:56:51,463
君の夢 憧れたヒーローに
To the hero your dreams admired,

733
00:56:51,463 --> 00:56:56,663
今すぐ させてあげよう
I will let you become him right now.

734
00:56:57,163 --> 00:57:01,163
雨みたいに 差し伸べられたって
Even if it was reached out to me like rain,

735
00:57:01,163 --> 00:57:05,663
嬉しくないんだ
I wouldn't be happy.

736
00:57:06,163 --> 00:57:10,663
敗北の少年 旋風を謳え
Defeated boy, sing of the whirlwind.

737
00:57:10,663 --> 00:57:15,663
君みたいに眩しくはなれないけど
I can't be radiant like you, but...

738
00:57:16,663 --> 00:57:21,663
こんな泥に 意味があるなら
If there's meaning in this mud,

739
00:57:21,663 --> 00:57:28,163
僕らは地を這う まだ地を這う
we will crawl on the ground, still crawl on the ground.

740
00:57:32,463 --> 00:57:38,163
あぁ...
Ah...

741
00:57:38,163 --> 00:57:45,163
あぁ...
Ah...

742
00:57:49,163 --> 00:57:53,663
鼓動を知って 息を吸い込んで
Feeling my heartbeat, taking a deep breath,

743
00:57:53,663 --> 00:57:57,163
僕は遠慮するよ
I'll pass.

744
00:57:57,163 --> 00:57:59,163
敗北の...
Defeated...

745
00:57:59,163 --> 00:58:03,663
敗北の少年 平凡を謳え
Defeated boy, sing of the ordinary.

746
00:58:03,663 --> 00:58:08,663
あいにく神は信じないタチで
Unfortunately, I'm not the type to believe in God.

747
00:58:08,663 --> 00:58:13,663
すれ違いの 物語よ サヨナラ
Goodbye, to our passing story.

748
00:58:17,163 --> 00:58:21,163
敗北の少年 現実を謳え
Defeated boy, sing of reality.

749
00:58:21,163 --> 00:58:27,163
僕らは泥を吐き這いつくばるもの
We are those who spit mud and crawl.

750
00:58:28,163 --> 00:58:32,663
こんな泥も 愛おしいから
Because even this mud is beloved,

751
00:58:32,663 --> 00:58:39,163
僕らは地を這う ただ地を這う
we will crawl on the ground, just crawl on the ground.

752
00:59:15,663 --> 00:59:16,963
あのね
Hey...

753
00:59:44,363 --> 00:59:46,163
I say "私、大丈夫?"
I say, 'Am I okay?'

754
00:59:46,163 --> 00:59:48,163
Maybe, うまくやれるはず
Maybe, I should be able to do it well.

755
00:59:48,163 --> 00:59:51,463
ずっと走った 息継ぎもしないまま
Running all the way without even taking a breath.

756
00:59:51,663 --> 00:59:53,463
あっそう、終わりが来るなら
Oh, if the end is coming,

757
00:59:53,463 --> 00:59:55,363
別に寂しくなんかはない
it's not like I'm lonely or anything.

758
00:59:55,363 --> 00:59:58,363
真実は 心の奥の方
The truth is deep in my heart.

759
00:59:58,363 --> 01:00:01,163
自分のことすら 愛せないまま
Without even being able to love myself...

760
01:00:00,138 --> 01:00:01,438
ないまま
...without even taking a breath...

761
01:00:01,438 --> 01:00:04,638
君のこと守れるのかな
can I protect you?

762
01:00:06,638 --> 01:00:10,038
どうか 正心正銘のこの思いを聴いて
Please, listen to this truly genuine feeling of mine

763
01:00:10,138 --> 01:00:13,638
私 全身全霊で歌うから
because I will sing with all my heart and soul

764
01:00:13,738 --> 01:00:16,938
大丈夫 世界はこんなに綺麗だと
It's okay, I understand that the world is so beautiful...

765
01:00:17,138 --> 01:00:20,338
分かってる 分かってる 分かってる 分かってるよ
I know, I know, I know, I do know!

766
01:00:20,338 --> 01:00:21,538
ごめんね じれったい
I'm sorry, it's frustrating.

767
01:00:21,538 --> 01:00:24,138
足りない こんなんじゃ誰 mo aisenai no
It's not enough, I can't love anyone like this

768
01:00:24,238 --> 01:00:27,538
止めない 止まることは知らないの
Don't stop, I don't know how to stop

769
01:00:27,638 --> 01:00:31,638
言葉足らず 失くしてしまう物ばかりだ
I'm just lacking words, constantly losing things

770
01:00:32,538 --> 01:00:36,138
Luna say maybe...

771
01:00:36,638 --> 01:00:41,638
降るのは 迷be, rainy
It's falling, Maybe, rainy

772
01:00:48,438 --> 01:00:49,938
愛せ どんな自分でも
Love yourself, no matter who you are

773
01:00:49,938 --> 01:00:51,938
Maybe, ネイビー色に染まるまで
Maybe, until it is dyed in navy

774
01:00:52,038 --> 01:00:55,338
時間はかかるかもしれないけど
It might take some time, but...

775
01:00:55,438 --> 01:00:58,638
I know, 輝くしかないこと
I know, there's no choice but to shine

776
01:00:58,638 --> 01:01:01,538
ハイライト 塗り続けるしかない
Highlight, I have no choice but to keep painting it

777
01:01:01,638 --> 01:01:04,338
真実はちゃんと 言わなくちゃね
I have to speak the truth clearly, right?

778
01:01:04,438 --> 01:01:07,638
目に見えるものが
To things that can be seen...

779
01:01:08,638 --> 01:01:13,638
続くと、ずっと そう、ずっと
continuing, forever... yes, forever.

780
01:01:15,638 --> 01:01:19,538
君に 半信半疑な素振りして
Acting half-doubting towards you,

781
01:01:19,638 --> 01:01:23,338
心 空回り 遠回り
My heart spins in circles, taking detours

782
01:01:23,338 --> 01:01:26,638
最低だ もう一回やり直せるのなら
It's the worst, if I could redo it one more time,

783
01:01:26,738 --> 01:01:30,138
素真になりたい なりたい なりたいと 願ったジレンマ
I want to be honest, I want to, I want to... my wished-for dilemma

784
01:01:30,138 --> 01:01:33,538
このまま 1人じゃ何もできない
At this rate, I can't do anything alone

785
01:01:33,538 --> 01:01:36,638
全部 決めるのは 自分次第
Everything is up to me to decide

786
01:01:36,638 --> 01:01:40,138
初めて背中をみた時に
When I first saw your back,

787
01:01:40,138 --> 01:01:43,738
覚悟を決めた どこまで
I made up my mind. How far...

788
01:01:43,838 --> 01:01:47,438
いけるのか
can I go?

789
01:01:47,538 --> 01:01:50,938
届くのか
Will I reach it?

790
01:01:50,938 --> 01:01:53,738
わからないよ
I don't know...

791
01:01:53,838 --> 01:01:57,638
臆病がそこに立っている
Cowardice is standing right there.

792
01:01:57,738 --> 01:02:01,138
3秒前バックステージ 震える背中を君に預けて
3 seconds before backstage, I entrust my trembling back to you

793
01:02:01,138 --> 01:02:04,638
この運命的出会いは きっと
This fated meeting is surely...

794
01:02:04,638 --> 01:02:08,638
そう、きっと
...yes, surely...

795
01:02:08,638 --> 01:02:11,638
偶然みたいな
...like a coincidence.

796
01:02:11,638 --> 01:02:15,138
多分、神様のいたずらです
Perhaps, it's a prank by God.

797
01:02:15,138 --> 01:02:18,638
どうか 正心正銘のこの思いが
Please, until this truly genuine feeling of mine...

798
01:02:18,638 --> 01:02:22,138
君の心(ところ)にちゃんと届くまで
...reaches your heart properly.

799
01:02:22,138 --> 01:02:25,638
ここで 私 全身全霊で歌うから
Here, I will sing with all my heart and soul, so...

800
01:02:25,638 --> 01:02:27,138
待ってる 待っている
I'm waiting, I'm waiting,

801
01:02:27,138 --> 01:02:28,938
だから、この場所を大切にしたいの
So, I want to cherish this place.

802
01:02:28,938 --> 01:02:32,138
これが 正心正銘の私なんだ
This is the truly genuine me!

803
01:02:32,138 --> 01:02:36,138
大丈夫 もう怖くはないわ
It's okay, I'm not afraid anymore!

804
01:02:36,138 --> 01:02:42,138
たまにつまずくことならあるけど
Sometimes I might stumble, but...

805
01:02:42,138 --> 01:02:46,138
一番特等席で 君の笑顔見たいんだ
I want to see your smile from the very best seat

806
01:02:46,138 --> 01:02:49,138
私だけの特権
My exclusive privilege

807
01:02:49,138 --> 01:02:53,138
見えない未来 手探り今日も
Even today, groping through an unseen future...

808
01:02:53,138 --> 01:02:57,138
ステージの上で 証明してみせるから
I'll prove it to you on this stage!

809
01:03:05,138 --> 01:03:09,638
ここにしかないスクリーンに
On the screen that only exists here...

810
01:03:17,138 --> 01:03:21,138
君にまだ話せてないこと
There are still things I haven't told you...

811
01:03:21,138 --> 01:03:24,138
ばかりあるんだ
...so many of them.

812
01:03:24,138 --> 01:03:28,138
聞いてほしいの
I want you to hear them...

813
01:03:28,138 --> 01:03:32,138
あのね...
You see...

814
01:03:56,138 --> 01:04:00,138
はあ... みんな、見に来てくれて本当にありがとう！
Phew... Everyone, thank you so much for coming to see me!

815
01:04:00,138 --> 01:04:03,138
最後は新曲をお届けします。
Lastly, I'll be delivering my new song.

816
01:04:03,138 --> 01:04:05,138
聞いてください。
Please listen.

817
01:04:11,138 --> 01:04:16,138
You & 合図
[Song: You & Aizu]

818
01:04:21,138 --> 01:04:23,138
目覚めの合図
The signal of awakening

819
01:04:23,138 --> 01:04:25,138
スマホが踊る
My smartphone dances

820
01:05:00,186 --> 01:05:01,986
...の合図
...our signal.

821
01:05:11,986 --> 01:05:13,486
もう一歩を
Take one more step...

822
01:05:13,486 --> 01:05:16,986
踏み出して
Step forward,

823
01:05:16,986 --> 01:05:19,186
踏み出して...
step forward,

824
01:05:19,186 --> 01:05:21,986
合わせてみよう
let's match them together!

825
01:05:22,686 --> 01:05:23,686
なんでマンデー
Why is it Monday?

826
01:05:23,686 --> 01:05:24,886
どうしてサンデー
Why is it Sunday?

827
01:05:24,886 --> 01:05:27,886
明日へ弾んでいたいの
I want to keep bouncing toward tomorrow!

828
01:05:27,886 --> 01:05:29,186
タクトをシュッ・シュッ
Baton: Swish, swish!

829
01:05:29,186 --> 01:05:30,486
拍手をパン・パン
Applause: Clap, clap!

830
01:05:30,486 --> 01:05:34,186
ここからはすべてダ・カーポ
From here on, it's all Da Capo!

831
01:05:34,186 --> 01:05:36,186
日曜日の...
Leaping over...

832
01:05:36,186 --> 01:05:41,486
コーダを飛び越えて
Sunday's Coda!

833
01:05:41,486 --> 01:05:43,186
待ってるよ
I'm waiting!

834
01:05:43,186 --> 01:05:45,486
明日よ...
Tomorrow...

835
01:05:45,486 --> 01:05:49,886
来ないでと願ってしまうほど
wishing so hard that it wouldn't come!

836
01:05:49,886 --> 01:05:54,186
(La La La)

837
01:05:54,186 --> 01:05:55,886
あなたを...
Even the time...

838
01:05:55,886 --> 01:06:04,386
待ちわびる時間すらも愛おしい
waiting for you is lovable!

839
01:06:04,986 --> 01:06:07,186
一歩前に
One step forward,

840
01:06:07,186 --> 01:06:10,186
レガート深呼吸
legato deep breath!

841
01:06:10,186 --> 01:06:12,186
スタッカートで
Staccato...

842
01:06:12,186 --> 01:06:15,686
二度の瞬き Compass
two blinks!

843
01:06:15,686 --> 01:06:18,686
月曜の約束を
Let's play our Monday promise!

844
01:06:18,686 --> 01:06:21,186
奏でよう
Let's play!

845
01:06:21,186 --> 01:06:22,186
ねえ、
Hey...

846
01:06:22,186 --> 01:06:25,686
君と僕の合図
the signal between you and me!

847
01:06:25,686 --> 01:06:33,686
(Na Na Na)

848
01:06:33,686 --> 01:06:36,186
奏でよう
Let's play!

849
01:06:36,186 --> 01:06:39,186
ね、叶うよ
Yeah, it will come true!

850
01:06:39,186 --> 01:06:43,186
私たちだけの合図保存
The signal only for us two!

851
01:06:50,986 --> 01:07:01,186
なんと！最後の曲は、奏自身の2作目の
オリ曲、「You & 合図」でしたー！パフパフ！
And that! The final song was Kanade's second
original song, "You & Aizu"! *Trumpet sounds*!

852
01:07:01,186 --> 01:07:04,686
てれれん！可愛いでしょう、新曲のジャケ写です！
Tada! Isn't it cute? This is the jacket art
for the new song!

853
01:07:04,686 --> 01:07:13,686
このあと24時、えっと21日の0時、あ、0時、
ちょっと噛んじゃいました、21日の0時から配信開始です！
After this, at 24:00—rather, at 0:00 on the 21st...
ah, 0:00... I bit my tongue a little, it starts streaming from 0:00 on the 21st!

854
01:07:13,686 --> 01:07:19,686
もうね、すごく可愛い振り付けとなっているので
良かったら踊ってみてね！
The choreography is super cute,
so please try dancing to it if you like!

855
01:07:19,686 --> 01:07:28,186
さらに、この配信のあとMVも、
えっと21時10分からプレミア公開されます！
Furthermore, after this stream, the MV will also
have its premiere starting at 21:10!

856
01:07:28,186 --> 01:07:39,186
もうこちらの楽曲ですね、あの歌詞もちらっと
見えていたから分か... ちょっと気づいてるお前らもね、
たくさんコメント欄でさ、ムカムカしていたと思うんですが...
With this song, since you could see glimpses
of the lyrics... I think some of you noticed and were
probably itching to say something in the comments, but...

857
01:07:39,186 --> 01:07:49,186
あの月曜日だったり、奏の要素がいっぱい込められている、
そういう楽曲となっているので良かったらね、あの、
いっぱい聴いてください！
It's a song filled with Kanade-like elements,
including references to Monday, so I hope
you listen to it a lot!

858
01:07:49,186 --> 01:07:51,686
はい！
Yes!

859
01:07:51,686 --> 01:08:00,186
えっと、ということで皆さんお待ちかねのグッズ情報も
行って参りたいと思います！MVも見てね！
So, let's move on to the merchandise info that
you've all been waiting for! Be sure to watch the MV too!

860
01:08:00,186 --> 01:08:05,686
えっと、えっと、音乃瀬奏生誕記念グッズ2026！
ぱんぱかぱーん！可愛い！
Um... Otonose Kanade Birthday Celebration
Merchandise 2026! *Fanfare*! So cute!

861
01:08:05,686 --> 01:08:14,686
配信開始はこのあと21時20分からだから安心してい
最後までちゃんと見ていってね。順番にしょって、
紹介していきます。まずは、こちら！てれれん！
Sales start after this at 21:20, so don't worry, relax and
make sure to watch until the very end. I'll introduce
them in order. First, this one! Tada!

862
01:08:14,686 --> 01:08:19,686
奏と待ち合わせ！ポストカードフレーム！
Kanade and Rendezvous! Postcard Frame!

863
01:08:19,686 --> 01:08:31,186
今回のキービジュアルを「奏と待ち合わせ」をテーマに
gomziママに描いていただきましたので、日常のワンシーンを
飾るイメージで作ってみました！可愛いでしょう！
For this key visual, we had gomzi-mama draw it based on
the theme "Rendezvous with Kanade", so we made it
with the idea of decorating a scene from your daily life! Isn't it cute?!

864
01:08:31,186 --> 01:08:37,686
そのままでも楽しめる他、他のポストカードだったり挟んで、
別の絵柄で楽しむこともできます。2つ目は、こちら！
In addition to enjoying it as it is, you can also
slide other postcards inside to enjoy different designs.
The second item is this!

865
01:08:37,686 --> 01:08:44,186
また奏が落書きしちゃったwTシャツ！
Kanade Scribbled Again T-Shirt!

866
01:08:44,186 --> 01:08:53,686
奏の落書きTシャツ第2弾！本当に今日は、月曜日！
もう月曜日盛りだくさんです。ハッピー月曜日！
This is the second volume of Kanade's scribble T-shirts!
Today really is Monday! Yes, it's packed with Mondays.
Happy Monday!

867
01:08:53,686 --> 01:09:02,186
ということで月曜日Tシャツです。毎週月曜日にはこの
Tシャツを着てね、良かったら生活してください。
最高、ありがとう！えっと、3つ目は、こちら！
So, it's a Monday T-shirt. Please wear this T-shirt
every Monday to live your daily life.
Awesome, thank you! Okay, the third item is this!

868
01:09:02,186 --> 01:09:06,186
奏とおそろネックレス！可愛いでしょう！
Matching Necklace with Kanade! Isn't it cute?!

869
01:09:06,186 --> 01:09:16,186
今回キービジュアルの奏との、おそろいの、
奏モチーフのネックレスです。確か、デビュー日が
書かれているはず。です、奏の。良かったら...
This is a Kanade-motif necklace that matches
the one worn by Kanade in the key visual.
I believe her debut date is engraved on it. Yes, Kanade's. If you like...

870
01:09:16,186 --> 01:09:25,686
えっと、すごいシンプルでスタイリッシュなデザインに
落とし込んでみたので、普段アクセサリー着けないよっていう
